      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOKYO ROSE NZ (8) drew wide and worked in the Queen Elizabeth II Mile last start but had strong form prior, getting within a nose of the top mare Eye Keep Smiling in the Robin Dundee two back. Won her first four tries at this circuit and distance so can return to winning from. STENO (9) has been terrific here of late, winning the Sibelia from a similar barrier two back then racing three wide without cover but digging deep for a brave second in the QE II Mile. Draws deeper than Tokyo Rose tonight but clearly beat her home last start. SOHO AMERICANO (11) was one of the top fillies of last season, her accolades including wins in both the Victoria and Queensland Oaks. Cops a wide draw for her return but has a decent record here and was readied with two trials. GUNNA RELOAD (10) draws deep but is racing well and her strike rate at the distance is impressive.",
